## Phase 5: Accessibility Pass (WCAG AA)

**Goal:** Ensure all screens meet WCAG AA standards

### 5.1 ARIA Labels (All 8 Screens)

#### Add to All Screens:
- [ ] `aria-label` on icon-only buttons (Edit, Delete, Archive, Save, Share)
- [ ] `aria-labelledby` on modals
- [ ] `aria-describedby` for form hints
- [ ] `role="status"` on loading spinners
- [ ] `role="alert"` on error messages

### 5.2 Keyboard Navigation

#### Modal Focus Management:
- [ ] Trap focus within modals when open
- [ ] Focus first input on modal open
- [ ] Return focus to trigger button on close
- [ ] Escape key closes modal

#### General Navigation:
- [ ] Ensure all interactive elements are tabbable
- [ ] Add visible focus indicators
- [ ] Skip links for screen readers

### 5.3 Color Contrast

#### Verify WCAG AA Compliance:
- [ ] Check all status badges (green, amber, red text on colored backgrounds)
- [ ] Verify gradient text on header (white on blue/indigo)
