## Verification Plan

### Automated Testing
- [ ] Run `npm run build` after each phase
- [ ] Verify 0 TypeScript errors
- [ ] Check bundle size (should not increase significantly)

### Manual Testing Checklist

#### Per Screen Testing:
- [ ] Load screen with no data → Empty state displays
- [ ] Trigger API error (disconnect network) → Error state displays with retry
- [ ] Test loading state → Skeleton displays (not full-screen spinner)
- [ ] Perform CRUD operation → Toast notification displays
- [ ] Test all buttons → All are functional
- [ ] Test keyboard navigation → All elements tabbable, modals trap focus
- [ ] Test screen reader → ARIA labels read correctly
- [ ] Test responsive (375px, 768px, 1920px) → Layout adapts

#### Cross-Screen Testing:
- [ ] Consistency: All modals look identical
- [ ] Consistency: All tables have same structure
- [ ] Consistency: All toasts have same styling
- [ ] Consistency: All empty states follow same pattern

### Accessibility Testing
- [ ] Run Lighthouse accessibility audit (target score: 95+)
- [ ] Test with keyboard only (no mouse)
- [ ] Test with screen reader (NVDA/JAWS)
- [ ] Verify color contrast with WebAIM contrast checker

