## Success Criteria

### Production-Ready Checklist
- [ ] All 8 screens have empty state handling
- [ ] All 8 screens have error state handling with retry
- [ ] All 8 screens have appropriate loading states (skeleton or spinner)
- [ ] Toast notifications on all user actions (success/error)
- [ ] All interactive buttons are functional
- [ ] All dropdowns are API-driven (no hardcoded data)
- [ ] All forms have validation with error messages
- [ ] All screens pass WCAG AA accessibility standards
- [ ] All screens pass Lighthouse accessibility audit (95+)
- [ ] Code duplication reduced by extracting reusable components
- [ ] Build passes with 0 errors
- [ ] Bundle size increase is minimal (<10%)

### Definition of Done
✅ **Production-Ready** when:
- Users never see broken UI (empty/error states prevent this)
- Users always get feedback (toasts confirm actions)
- Users can navigate with keyboard (accessibility)
- Code is maintainable (reusable components)
- No technical debt remains from initial conversion

